You’re asking:

What is metadata here?
Is it metadata of SAML response?

No ❌ — it is NOT metadata of a single SAML response.

It is something much bigger.

🔐 What Is IdP Metadata in SAML?

IdP Metadata is an XML document that describes the Identity Provider configuration.

It tells your Rails app:

Who the IdP is

Where to send authentication requests

Which certificates to trust

Which bindings are supported

It is like a configuration contract between SP and IdP.

🏢 In Case of Active Directory Federation Services

ADFS exposes a metadata URL like:

https://adfs.company.com/FederationMetadata/2007-06/FederationMetadata.xml

That XML is the IdP metadata.

🧠 What Is Inside Metadata?

Example (simplified):

<EntityDescriptor entityID="https://adfs.company.com/adfs/services/trust">
  
  <IDPSSODescriptor>
    
    <SingleSignOnService 
        Binding="urn:oasis:names:tc:SAML:2.0:bindings:HTTP-Redirect"
        Location="https://adfs.company.com/adfs/ls/" />

    <KeyDescriptor use="signing">
      <KeyInfo>
        <X509Data>
          <X509Certificate>
            MIIDdzCCAl+gAwIBAgIEbG3...
          </X509Certificate>
        </X509Data>
      </KeyInfo>
    </KeyDescriptor>

  </IDPSSODescriptor>
</EntityDescriptor>

That contains:

Entity ID

SSO URL

Signing certificate(s)

Supported protocols

Bindings

🔁 So Metadata Is NOT:

❌ Not per user
❌ Not inside SAML response
❌ Not dynamic per request

It is static configuration describing the IdP.

🏗 Why Metadata Matters for Certificate Rotation

When ADFS rotates certificates:

The metadata XML updates like this:

<KeyDescriptor use="signing">
  <X509Certificate>OLD_CERT</X509Certificate>
</KeyDescriptor>

<KeyDescriptor use="signing">
  <X509Certificate>NEW_CERT</X509Certificate>
</KeyDescriptor>

So SP can trust both during transition.

If Rails consumes metadata dynamically:

It automatically sees new certificate.

If Rails uses hardcoded certificate:

It breaks after switch.

🧠 Think of Metadata Like This

Metadata = Identity Provider’s public profile.

It says:

“Here is who I am, here are my endpoints, here are my certificates.”

🎯 Interview-Level Answer

If interviewer asks:

What is IdP metadata in SAML?

You say:

IdP metadata is an XML configuration document that describes the Identity Provider’s SAML endpoints, supported bindings, entity ID, and signing certificates. The Service Provider consumes this metadata to configure trust and validate SAML responses, especially during certificate rotation.

🔥 That’s very strong.

💥 Now Important Distinction
Thing	Purpose
SAML Response	Authentication message per login
IdP Metadata	Static configuration of IdP

